tabetic.d:
a. Of or pertaining to tabes; of the nature of tabes;
   affected with tabes; tabid.
n. One affected with tabes.

tache.d:
n. Something used for taking hold or holding; a catch; a loop;
   a button.
n. A spot, stain, or blemish.

talismanical.d:
a. Of or pertaining to a talisman; having the properties
   of a talisman, or preservative against evils by occult influence;
   magical.

tallowing.d:
p. pr. & vb. n. of Tallow
n. The act, or art, of causing animals to produce tallow;
   also, the property in animals of producing tallow.

tared.d:
imp. & p. p. of Tare
a. Weighed; determined; reduced to equal or standard weight;
   as, tared filter papers, used in weighing precipitates.
